actor constructor `newRedisStore` to return `(*redisStore, error)` -- PARTIALLY DONE (returns `(Store, error)` not `(*redisStore, error)`)\n- **T8**: Update Redis unit tests for new interface -- NOT DONE (tests still use old signatures)\n- **T9**: Race detection and gate verification -- NOT DONE\n\n### 3. Go Files in `pkg/store/` Directory\n\n| File | Path | Lines | Description |\n|------|------|-------|-------------|\n| **store.go** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store.go` | 35 | Store interface definition with **OLD signatures** (uses `GetSandbox`, `StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID string, info)`, `limit int`) and `ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"sandbox not found\")` |\n| **store_redis.go** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_redis.go` | 274 | Redis implementation -- has `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` using MGET, `ExpiresAt.IsZero()` check, but uses **OLD interface signatures** |\n| **store_valkey.go** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | 253 | Valkey implementation -- similar pattern, OLD signatures, but `ListExpiredSandboxes`/`ListInactiveSandboxes` use **individual GET calls** (not MGET batch) |\n| **singleton.go** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/singleton.go` | 39 | sync.Once singleton with STORE_TYPE routing, already handles error from `newRedisStore()` |\n| **codec.go** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/codec.go` | 19 | JSON encode/decode helpers |\n| **store_redis_test.go** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_redis_test.go` | 583 | 30+ test functions using OLD interface signatures |\n| **store_valkey_test.go** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go` | (exists) | Valkey tests |\n| **singleton_test.go** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/singleton_test.go` | 85 | Singleton/concurrent access tests |\n| **codec_test.go** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/codec_test.go` | 111 | Codec round-trip and error tests |\n\n### 4. Key Discrepancies Between Current Code and AR-013 Spec\n\n| Aspect | Current Code (AR-012) | AR-013 Target Spec |\n|--------|----------------------|-------------------|\n| `ErrNotFound` message | `\"sandbox not found\"` | `\"store: not found\"` |\n| Get method | `GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID string)` | `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string)` |\n| StoreSandbox | `StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID string, info *SandboxInfo)` | `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandboxStore *SandboxInfo)` |\n| UpdateSandbox | `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sessionID string, info *SandboxInfo)` | `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandboxStore *SandboxInfo)` |\n| List limit type | `limit int` | `limit int64` |\n| Redis client type | `redis.UniversalClient` | `*redis.Client` |\n| `newRedisStore` return | `(Store, error)` | `(*redisStore, error)` |\n| Redis ping in constructor | Not present | Required (`cli.Ping(ctx)`) |\n| Valkey List methods | Individual `GetSandbox` calls in loop | Should use `MGET` batch via `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` |\n\n### 5. Session Store Spec/Design (Base Reference)\n\n| File | Path | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| **spec.md** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/session-store/spec.md` | 118-line canonical specification defining the Store interface contract, error semantics, key naming, ZSET indices, etc. |\n| **design.md** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/session-store/design.md` | 206-line design reference with exact interface signatures, Redis/Valkey implementation details, and operations summary |\n\n### 6. Root-Level Design Document\n\n| File | Path | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| **design.md** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md` | 687-line \"AR-012: Session Store Interface Definition -- Design\" document. Contains the **target/canonical** interface signatures (the AR-013 spec), full implementation code examples for both Redis and Valkey, testing strategy, and future changes |\n\n### 7. Future Changes / Known Limitations / Deferred Work\n\nFrom `changes/AR-013/design.md` (Section 8, lines 693-707):\n\n| Change | Description | Priority |\n|--------|-------------|----------|\n| AR-0XX | TTL on session keys for automatic cleanup | P1 |\n| AR-0XX | Hash tag support for Redis Cluster slot affinity | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | Metrics: store operation latency, error rates | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | Connection pool tuning via environment variables | P3 |\n\n**Known Limitations:**\n- No automatic TTL on session JSON keys; relies on GC controller for cleanup\n- `MGET` in `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` assumes single-slot keys for cluster deployments\n- No pagination for `List*` methods beyond simple `limit` parameter\n- `SETNX` in `StoreSandbox` prevents updates; use `UpdateSandbox` for modifications\n\n### 8. Out of Scope (from AR-013 proposal.md, lines 65-71)\n\n- `ListSandboxes` method spec alignment (not defined in spec, kept as-is)\n- Helm Chart or deployment config changes\n- K8s CRD or client-go changes\n- Router, Reconciler, GC component caller adaptation (covered by their own ARs)\n- Valkey cluster mode hash slot issues (noted in code comments)\n\n### 9. Git Log\n\nNo commits found mentioning \"AR-013\" or \"redis\" -- the repository appears to have no git history (likely a fresh workspace or uncommitted state).\n\n### 10. TODO/BACKLOG/Archive Files\n\n- **No** `TODO`, `BACKLOG`, `archive`, or `notes` files exist anywhere in the workspace.\n- The `changes/AR-012/design.md` file contains 9 `<!-- TODO: ... -->` placeholders (all sections are stubs), indicating that AR-012's design document was never fully filled in -- the canonical design lives in the root-level `design.md` instead.\n- The `changes/AR-012/tasks.md` file shows AR-012 at \"Stage ST-3 (Design Complete)\" with all file outputs marked as \"confirmed\" or \"new\", meaning AR-012's implementation is done but AR-013 (the alignment/refactoring work) has not started.\n\n### 11. Project Context\n\nFrom `project.md`: The project is **AgentCube** -- a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents, module path `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`. Storage layer uses Redis (`go-redis/v9`) and Valkey (`valkey-go`).\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_287edbec2ffeampNqkLbnwOaW6","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Find AR-013 Redis storage","time":{"start":1775835955515,"end":1775836136809}}}}
